            },
            "answer_text": "I see a lot of yes and nos among different answers here. Let me share the complete story. Previously, there was no restrictions on IIT/NIT admission in terms of drops or number of attempts. During my time of admission 2007, the attempts to JEE got reduced to 2. You could appear for 2 consecutive times.  Just after this norm, came another which started checking the drop years in order to restrict the number of people who delay their time in getting admitted. Since, then the Ministry of Human Resources and development started asking for GAP certificate. Below is a sample copy of one such certificate. http://www.nith.ac.in/rdesk/gap-study.pdf  ",
